The paper discusses an algorithm for inverse reinforcement learning (IRL) that uses Conditional Choice Probabilities (CCP) and makes connections to existing results in econometrics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Robotics (cs.RO), Economics (cs.EC), or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely as they are the primary sub-categories for machine learning and artificial intelligence research, respectively. cs.RO is also likely as the paper discusses the application of IRL in robotics. cs.EC is a possibility as the paper makes connections to econometrics. cs.CE is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the practical benefits of the algorithm.
